==English==
===Etymology===
French [[amiable]], Latin [[amicabilis]] friendly, from [[amicus]] friend, from [[amare]] to love. The meaning has been influenced by French [[aimable]], Latin [[amabilis]] lovable, from [[amare]] to love. Compare with [[Amicable]], [[Amorous]], [[Amability]].

===Pronunciation===
IPA: [[WEAE]] /ˈeɪ.mi.ə.bəl/

===Adjective===
# Friendly; kindly; sweet; gracious; as, an amiable temper or mood; amiable ideas.
# Possessing sweetness of disposition; having sweetness of temper, kind-heartedness, etc., which causes one to be liked; as, an amiable woman.
